1
00:00:02,839 --> 00:00:06,565
Here we’re making 
a distinction, 
 

2
00:00:06,565 --> 00:00:11,485
we’re defining, 
connotating,

3
00:00:11,485 --> 00:00:15,368
we’re increasing the connotation 
of what is meant by ‘heart’,

4
00:00:15,368 --> 00:00:18,326
[Robinson Crusoe | Desert Island of Ego]

5
00:00:18,334 --> 00:00:25,470
because from 
a mundane point of view

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,880
in the 7th chapter 
of the Bhagavad-gītā Kṛṣṇa says,

7
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:35,767
bhūmir āpo ’nalo vāyuḥ
khaṁ mano buddhir eva ca
 

8
00:00:35,767 --> 00:00:40,367
ahaṅkāra itīyaṁ me
bhinnā prakṛtir aṣṭadhā
[Bg: 7.4]

9
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:46,629
He outlines sequentially 
what are the eight material elements:

10
00:00:46,629 --> 00:00:50,343
bhūmir āpo ’nalo vāyuḥ
[Cc: 2.6.164],

11
00:00:50,343 --> 00:00:56,823
earth, water, fire, air, ether, 
mind, and intelligence,

12
00:00:56,823 --> 00:01:00,283
and ahaṅkāra—
false ego.

13
00:01:01,463 --> 00:01:05,488
In the following śloka
He says,

14
00:01:05,498 --> 00:01:10,227
apareyam itas tv anyāṁ
prakṛtiṁ viddhi me parām
 

15
00:01:10,227 --> 00:01:15,707
jīva-bhūtāṁ mahā-bāho
yayedaṁ dhāryate jagat
[Bg: 7.5]

16
00:01:15,707 --> 00:01:20,282
He says that, 
“But the jīva, jīva-śakti …

17
00:01:20,282 --> 00:01:30,092
(what I’ve just outlined 
is prakṛti—mundane energy)

18
00:01:30,102 --> 00:01:35,542
jīva is a superior
type of  śakti,

19
00:01:37,452 --> 00:01:40,682
which is above
these eight elements.”

20
00:01:41,372 --> 00:01:46,723
So although we don’t normally 
think of it this way, it’s not the first verse 
 

21
00:01:46,723 --> 00:01:50,263
that would come to our mind 
in terms of sahajiyāism.

22
00:01:50,303 --> 00:01:56,126
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj used it 
as a refutation of  sahajiyāism.

23
00:01:57,436 --> 00:02:02,499
Along these lines that their idea 
is that by reconditioning

24
00:02:02,499 --> 00:02:07,739
the element of mind, 
the mundane element of mind,

25
00:02:07,739 --> 00:02:11,076
filling it with images 
of Kṛṣṇa,

26
00:02:11,076 --> 00:02:14,666
making it accustomed 
to hearing certain sounds,

27
00:02:14,666 --> 00:02:19,419
that one will have 
some sort of epiphany,

28
00:02:19,419 --> 00:02:23,979
and their swarūp
will manifest.

29
00:02:25,819 --> 00:02:31,859
Guru Mahārāj is of the opinion 
that all of this must dissolve.

30
00:02:35,009 --> 00:02:38,119
Because the subtlest aspect 
is ahaṅkāra, false ego,

31
00:02:38,119 --> 00:02:40,289
but then the buddhi, 
the mind, 
 

32
00:02:40,289 --> 00:02:42,719
the body that’s housing 
these elements—

33
00:02:42,719 --> 00:02:47,279
all of these
must be dissolved.

34
00:02:47,839 --> 00:02:50,839
In what way? Or …
Gurudev gave a famous lecture called

35
00:02:50,839 --> 00:02:53,855
“Dissolving the pillars of ego.”

36
00:02:54,385 --> 00:02:57,385
“Demolishing the pillars of ego.”

37
00:02:57,385 --> 00:03:04,842
How? Not through some 
Buddhistic type of dissolution,

38
00:03:04,842 --> 00:03:11,762
but rather through service,

39
00:03:11,762 --> 00:03:14,882
through service engagement, 
through dedication.

40
00:03:15,232 --> 00:03:19,696
Biological expression 
of the soul’s delusion is the body.

41
00:03:19,696 --> 00:03:25,966
It’s the outcome of jīva’s 
exploiting tendency,

42
00:03:26,596 --> 00:03:30,506
the desire 
to lord over matter.

43
00:03:30,786 --> 00:03:34,066
Sometimes he would quote 
“Robinson Crusoe”.

44
00:03:34,066 --> 00:03:39,916
Alexander Selkirk, the famous …
The man shipwrecked on the island.

45
00:03:39,916 --> 00:03:43,816
And he has a line, where he says, 
“I am the lord of all I survey.”

46
00:03:43,816 --> 00:03:44,937
So he’s saying,

47
00:03:44,937 --> 00:03:49,187
“This mood, this mania
that I’m the master

48
00:03:49,797 --> 00:03:55,187
and detesting 
the very notion of …

49
00:03:55,487 --> 00:04:03,107
servitude or,
by extension, slavery,

50
00:04:03,107 --> 00:04:07,317
being subordinate,
being submissive.”

51
00:04:07,637 --> 00:04:14,361
In modern times any qualities 
associated with this notion

52
00:04:14,361 --> 00:04:21,621
are considered undesirable 
and detrimental

53
00:04:21,621 --> 00:04:27,524
to developing oneself
and one’s self-esteem, etc.

54
00:04:27,646 --> 00:04:31,655
So the body is a biological expression 
of the soul’s delusion,

55
00:04:31,655 --> 00:04:34,975
that includes mind,
intelligence,

56
00:04:34,975 --> 00:04:38,952
but the outcome 
of exploiting tendency,

57
00:04:38,952 --> 00:04:42,842
the biological outcome 
of exploiting tendency,

58
00:04:42,842 --> 00:04:48,496
if we become connected 
to the service plane,

59
00:04:48,506 --> 00:04:52,356
if we withdraw
from being exploiting agents

60
00:04:52,356 --> 00:04:55,806
and become enriched 
with a dedicating tendency,

61
00:04:55,806 --> 00:05:02,612
then the body, 
mind, intelligence,

62
00:05:02,612 --> 00:05:05,302
which were the outcome 
of the exploiting tendency,

63
00:05:05,302 --> 00:05:12,472
start to vanish, 
and the spiritual mind, intellect, body

64
00:05:12,472 --> 00:05:15,556
begin to manifest—the swarūp.

